KABUL, Dec. 6 (Xinhua) -- Afghan security forces have rescued a boy from the clutch of kidnappers in Afghanistan's northern Balkh province, the state-run news agency Bakhtar reported Monday. The forces, according to the news agency, discovered the boy from the kidnappers' hand in the Balkh provincial capital Mazar-i-Sharif city on Sunday, and police have arrested eight persons in this regard. This is the second person who has been released from kidnappers over the past week. Earlier the security forces rescued a child from Mazar-i-Sharif city on Thursday. Enditem